r","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"This class is a piece of fake UI that is intended to mimic "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PKAddPaymentPassViewController"},{"type":"text","text":". That class is restricted to apps with a special entitlement from Apple, and as such can be difficult to build and test against. This class implements the same public API as "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PKAddPaymentPassViewController"},{"type":"text","text":", and can be used to develop against the Stripe API in "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"testmode only","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":". (Obviously it will not actually place cards into the user’s Apple Pay wallet either.) When it’s time to go to production, you may simply replace all references to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"STPFakeAddPaymentPassViewController"},{"type":"text","text":" in your app with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PKAddPaymentPassViewController"},{"type":"text","text":" and it will continue to function. For more information on developing against this API, please see https:\/\/stripe.com\/docs\/issuing\/cards\/digital-wallets ."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.stripe.stripe-issuing-push-provision\/documentation\/StripeIssuing\/STPFakeAddPaymentPassViewController","url":"\/documentation\/stripeissuing\/stpfakeaddpaymentpassviewcontroller","type":"topic"}}}